  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: the clinical operating envelope was extended in Q3 2025 to include paediatric patients (body surface area 0.5–1.2 m²) and reduced flow rates (1.0–2.5 L/min) following a post-market label expansion; the original validation campaign was conducted exclusively on adult haemodynamic conditions (2.5–6.0 L/min, BSA 1.5–2.2 m²). The assessment team judged that the prior validation results are sufficiently conservative to cover the expanded envelope without additional experimental correlation.",
