      "rationale": "GCI study (ValidationResult morrison-cpb-mesh-convergence-2024) demonstrates GCI = 2.1% at the adult nominal operating point (4.0 L/min, 2800 RPM). The team notes that GCI was not separately computed at paediatric flow rates (1.0–2.5 L/min); however, lower Reynolds number conditions are expected to be less sensitive to discretization error, and the adult GCI is considered representative."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions match simulated conditions within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Adult bench test conditions (flow rate ±0.05 L/min, rotational speed ±15 RPM, temperature 37±0.5°C) are well-characterised and reproduced in CFD boundary conditions. Paediatric operating conditions were not tested experimentally; the assessment team asserts that the boundary condition specification methodology is identical and introduces no additional uncertainty beyond that already characterised."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH index within ±15% of measured values across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Across the five adult validation operating points, maximum RH index prediction error was 11.8% (ValidationResult morrison-cpb-adult-bench-2024). Acceptance criterion of ±15% is satisfied. No experimental RH measurements exist for the paediatric flow regime (1.0–2.5 L/min); the team considers the adult error bound sufficient to infer model adequacy for the expanded envelope."
