      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative haemolysis index (RH < 1) consistent with ASTM F1841 and the predicate comparison framework. Volume-averaged shear stress and Lagrangian exposure time are secondary QoIs. All QoIs are directly used in the regulatory decision. Relevance is unchanged by the paediatric expansion because the same haemolysis metric applies."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments span the operating envelope defined in the COU, or the extrapolation distance is justified by physical similarity arguments.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments (morrison-cpb-adult-bench-2024) covered the original adult operating envelope (2.5–6.0 L/min). The COU operating envelope was subsequently extended to include paediatric patients at 1.0–2.5 L/min following label expansion in Q3 2025. The assessment team argues that the power-law haemolysis model is monotonically dependent on shear stress magnitude, and that adult shear levels at 2.5 L/min represent a conservative bound relative to paediatric shear levels at the same flow rate, making the adult validation dataset representative. No additional validation experiments covering the paediatric sub-range have been conducted or are linked to this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residuals converge to < 1e-5 for all transport equations; mass imbalance < 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations achieved residual convergence to < 1e-6 for continuity and momentum; mass imbalance < 0.005%. Iterative solver error is negligible relative to discretization and model-form uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
