      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; checklist completed.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup performed by a second qualified CFD analyst. Review checklist archived. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence and haemolysis sub-models are appropriate for the flow regime and are calibrated against relevant experimental data.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model and Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law haemolysis model selected based on published literature for centrifugal blood pumps. Model constants were not re-calibrated for paediatric blood rheology; the team notes that neonatal haematocrit variability (35–55%) falls within the range used in the original calibration datasets and is therefore considered covered."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Inlet velocity profiles, fluid properties, and geometric tolerances are characterised with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Fluid properties (viscosity, density) characterised at 37°C for adult bovine blood surrogate. Geometric tolerances from manufacturing drawings applied as parametric uncertainty (±0.05 mm on critical clearances). Inlet profiles derived from Womersley solution for adult cardiac output range. Paediatric cardiac output profiles were not separately characterised; adult inlet profiles are used at scaled flow rates."
    },
